- BECCA: Hutch!

515
00:26:24,142 --> 00:26:25,499
(scoffing):
God.

516
00:26:25,536 --> 00:26:26,767
Dad.

517
00:26:26,803 --> 00:26:28,311
(horn honking)

518
00:26:28,345 --> 00:26:30,270
BECCA:
<i>S-Sir, we were attacked.</i>

519
00:26:30,306 --> 00:26:32,175
<i>And I don't understand
why we're here.</i>

520
00:26:32,210 --> 00:26:34,516
I don't understand why
those bullies are not here.

521
00:26:34,550 --> 00:26:36,011
Are we being charged
with anything?

522
00:26:36,046 --> 00:26:38,154
Okay, is your son
prone to violence?

523
00:26:38,190 --> 00:26:40,152
Is my... Are you kidding me?

524
00:26:40,188 --> 00:26:42,315
Ma'am.

525
00:26:42,351 --> 00:26:45,018
I'm just trying to gather
some information.

526
00:26:45,054 --> 00:26:46,460
Uh, can you tell me exactly...

527
00:26:46,495 --> 00:26:48,125
Sir, if we're not being charged,

528
00:26:48,161 --> 00:26:49,831
I'd rather not answer
any more of your questions.

529
00:26:51,569 --> 00:26:55,236
I understand protecting
your sister, Brady.

530
00:26:55,270 --> 00:26:57,733
It's instinctual.

531
00:26:57,768 --> 00:26:59,067
But... (clears throat)

532
00:26:59,103 --> 00:27:01,501
there are other ways
to handle things.

533
00:27:02,706 --> 00:27:04,642
You serious?

534
00:27:04,678 --> 00:27:06,042
Y-You tell me to stay cool,

535
00:27:06,076 --> 00:27:08,342
but then you go
and lose your shit?

536
00:27:08,376 --> 00:27:10,486
Which I-I thought was awesome,
by the way.

537
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:11,877
- You know, the way that you...
- No.

538
00:27:11,913 --> 00:27:14,319
No, it wasn't.

539
00:27:14,355 --> 00:27:15,987
I'm just saying,

540
00:27:16,021 --> 00:27:20,227
you have to be better
than your old man.

541
00:27:20,263 --> 00:27:21,730
(Hutch sighs)

542
00:27:22,727 --> 00:27:24,097
(Brady scoffs)

543
00:27:24,133 --> 00:27:25,603
Whatever.

544
00:27:27,466 --> 00:27:31,400
(banging)

545
00:27:33,144 --> 00:27:35,238
(banging continues)

546
00:27:44,254 --> 00:27:46,516
(chuckles softly)

547
00:27:46,550 --> 00:27:47,957
Okay.

548
00:27:47,991 --> 00:27:49,255
Let's go.

549
00:27:49,289 --> 00:27:51,421
Get up.

550
00:27:51,457 --> 00:27:52,863
Not you.

551
00:27:52,898 --> 00:27:54,290
Just Dad.

552
00:28:01,006 --> 00:28:03,898
♪ ♪

553
00:28:03,932 --> 00:28:05,807
Sit your ass down.

554
00:28:11,842 --> 00:28:14,079
(chair creaking)

555
00:28:15,285 --> 00:28:17,083
You know who I am?

556
00:28:21,525 --> 00:28:23,153
(clears throat)
No, but, uh,

557
00:28:23,190 --> 00:28:25,794
the way you're sitting
behind the sheriff's desk,

558
00:28:25,828 --> 00:28:27,988
- I'm guessing you're somebody.
- Damn right I am.

559
00:28:28,024 --> 00:28:30,294
Name's Wyatt Martin.

560
00:28:31,432 --> 00:28:32,826
I run this town.

561
00:28:32,863 --> 00:28:34,601
Oh. I'm Hutch...

562
00:28:34,635 --> 00:28:36,472
I already know who you are.

563
00:28:36,508 --> 00:28:38,936
You're the tourist
fucked up my son.

564
00:28:38,970 --> 00:28:41,136
- I didn't...
- Shut the fuck up.

565
00:28:41,171 --> 00:28:43,079
Your son was the kid
at the arcade?

566
00:28:43,114 --> 00:28:45,716
Shut the fuck up.

567
00:28:47,115 --> 00:28:49,486
HUTCH: Well, your son may have
had something to do with...

568
00:28:49,520 --> 00:28:52,752
Your son has got
an attitude problem.

569
00:28:52,787 --> 00:28:54,120
And I'm pretty sure
I'm staring at...

570
00:28:56,319 --> 00:28:59,026
My daddy built this town,
and he had a rule.

571
00:29:00,023 --> 00:29:01,790
Tourists get a free pass.

572
00:29:01,826 --> 00:29:03,156
You know why, right?

573
00:29:03,191 --> 00:29:05,795
Bread and butter and all that?

574
00:29:05,829 --> 00:29:07,231
But for this...

575
00:29:08,306 --> 00:29:10,138
...your son... Brady, right?

576
00:29:10,172 --> 00:29:11,641
Yeah.

577
00:29:11,677 --> 00:29:14,636
Your son Brady messed up
my son's pitching arm.

578
00:29:14,671 --> 00:29:16,813
I get it.

579
00:29:17,806 --> 00:29:19,314
Do you?

580
00:29:19,348 --> 00:29:20,680
Yeah, I get it.

581
00:29:20,715 --> 00:29:23,982
I'll make my son apologize.

582
00:29:24,018 --> 00:29:26,655
But you should watch
the security cam footage,

583
00:29:26,690 --> 00:29:29,158
'cause one of those guys
smacked my daughter

584
00:29:29,193 --> 00:29:31,623
and I lost it.

585
00:29:31,659 --> 00:29:33,362
(takes deep breath)

586
00:29:33,396 --> 00:29:35,325
What would you have done?

587
00:29:45,276 --> 00:29:47,001
Walk 'em out.

588
00:29:47,037 --> 00:29:49,240
BECCA:
Brady, come on.

589
00:29:51,449 --> 00:29:53,710
So that's it, then? We can go?

590
00:29:53,747 --> 00:29:55,876
Do yourself a favor.

591
00:29:55,911 --> 00:29:57,248
Keep going.

592
00:30:07,595 --> 00:30:09,392
Get the boys together.

593
00:30:09,428 --> 00:30:11,097
DEPUTY DANN: Didn't Wyatt say
to leave them alone?

594
00:30:11,133 --> 00:30:13,103
SHERIFF ABEL: I don't
give a fuck what Wyatt says.

595
00:30:13,139 --> 00:30:14,694
Get rid of them.

596
00:30:19,903 --> 00:30:21,605
(camera clicks)

597
00:30:21,641 --> 00:30:22,978
Can you not?

598
00:30:32,456 --> 00:30:35,225
What the hell, Hutch?

599
00:30:35,259 --> 00:30:36,851
