630
00:32:09,854 --> 00:32:13,252
I knew who you were
the moment I met you.

631
00:32:15,219 --> 00:32:17,727
I knew you were dangerous.

632
00:32:17,763 --> 00:32:20,793
(laughing):
You were covered in blood.

633
00:32:20,827 --> 00:32:23,694
- (sighs)
- Good times.

634
00:32:23,729 --> 00:32:25,460
Good times.

635
00:32:25,495 --> 00:32:28,432
("Run Run Run" by Jo Jo Gunne
playing)

636
00:32:29,836 --> 00:32:31,198
♪ Run, run... ♪

637
00:32:31,232 --> 00:32:33,309
Holy crap, Mom.

638
00:32:33,344 --> 00:32:35,076
You've got an eye.

639
00:32:37,405 --> 00:32:40,246
- (chuckles) Really?
- Yeah.

640
00:32:40,282 --> 00:32:43,352
This is not a fair fight.
This is not a fair fight.

641
00:32:43,387 --> 00:32:44,985
I'm on her side!

642
00:32:45,019 --> 00:32:46,651
- (birds chirping)
- (insects trilling)

643
00:32:46,686 --> 00:32:49,091
(humming)

644
00:32:50,428 --> 00:32:51,719
♪ Run ♪

645
00:32:53,699 --> 00:32:54,862
- ♪ Run... ♪
- HUTCH: Sammy.

646
00:32:54,896 --> 00:32:56,326
- Where'd she go?
- (camera winding)

647
00:32:56,362 --> 00:32:58,028
- (camera clicks)
- Sammy. Sammy, wait for me.

648
00:32:58,065 --> 00:33:00,526
- Dad, guess where I am.
- Oh!

649
00:33:00,562 --> 00:33:02,332
- (Sammy laughing)
- You got me.

650
00:33:02,366 --> 00:33:03,998
I warned you,
this is a wonderland.

651
00:33:04,034 --> 00:33:05,174
Off we go.

652
00:33:05,210 --> 00:33:06,603
Ready?

653
00:33:07,746 --> 00:33:09,979
- (camera clicks)
- (laughs) Supercute.

654
00:33:11,141 --> 00:33:12,545
(camera clicks)

655
00:33:12,579 --> 00:33:14,115
(laughs)

656
00:33:22,092 --> 00:33:24,527
HUTCH: Grandpa doesn't know
what he's missing.

657
00:33:24,562 --> 00:33:26,554
Duck boats are super fun.

658
00:33:26,588 --> 00:33:28,696
They're trustworthy,
but they don't...

659
00:33:28,730 --> 00:33:30,230
Four tickets for the...

660
00:33:31,726 --> 00:33:34,363
Th-That's...
that's not a duck boat.

661
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:36,104
Uh, yeah, you see
the big duck on the top?

662
00:33:36,140 --> 00:33:40,700
No, I told my son a duck boat
is a military vehicle.

663
00:33:40,736 --> 00:33:44,604
Uh, more than...
more than one conflict.

664
00:33:44,640 --> 00:33:46,875
I'm gonna...
Okay, four tickets.

665
00:33:46,911 --> 00:33:48,212
One kid.

666
00:33:48,248 --> 00:33:50,414
Yeah, here, honey,
hand these out.

667
00:33:50,450 --> 00:33:53,145
- (Becca laughing)
- Really heavy-duty. Mil spec.

668
00:33:53,181 --> 00:33:54,649
Yeah.

669
00:33:54,684 --> 00:33:58,322
BRADY: Single-handedly
caused our loss at 'Nam.

670
00:33:58,356 --> 00:34:00,219
GUIDE: Hey, only
a few seats left, folks.

671
00:34:00,255 --> 00:34:01,556
Come aboard.

672
00:34:01,591 --> 00:34:03,626
I hope you don't mind
getting wet.

673
00:34:04,635 --> 00:34:07,135
BECCA:
Yes. Thank you.

674
00:34:10,699 --> 00:34:12,101
Sweetie, why don't you
sit down there?

675
00:34:12,137 --> 00:34:14,273
Uh, that's good. Thanks.

676
00:34:14,309 --> 00:34:16,505
SAMMY: Dad's right.
It's like a bus that floats.

677
00:34:16,539 --> 00:34:18,941
BECCA:
It is like a bus that floats.

678
00:34:18,978 --> 00:34:20,545
Where is Dad?

679
00:34:22,445 --> 00:34:24,019
(stammers) You're not coming?

680
00:34:24,054 --> 00:34:26,753
Hon, I had too many churros
with my macchiato.

681
00:34:26,789 --> 00:34:28,481
I'll see you at the park.

682
00:34:28,516 --> 00:34:31,454
- BECCA: What? No.
- Have fun.

683
00:34:31,490 --> 00:34:34,094
- BRADY: Bye, Macchiato.
- Well... eat better!

684
00:34:34,128 --> 00:34:36,659
(duck quacking sound effects
blasting)

685
00:34:39,800 --> 00:34:41,829
(quiet chatter)

686
00:34:44,376 --> 00:34:46,802
♪ ♪

687
00:34:57,353 --> 00:34:59,177
Looks like it's the end
of the line for you, pal...

688
00:34:59,213 --> 00:35:01,820
BOAT DRIVER: All right, let's
get this party started. Vests.

689
00:35:01,856 --> 00:35:03,019
Grab 'em off my arm.

690
00:35:03,056 --> 00:35:04,521
- Vest?
- I'm good.

691
00:35:04,556 --> 00:35:05,961
- Excuse us. Oh, hi.
- Excuse us. Excuse us.

692
00:35:05,996 --> 00:35:07,557
- Yeah, yeah. Absolutely.
- Right up front?

693
00:35:07,594 --> 00:35:08,898
BOAT DRIVER: Just head on up
to the front, yeah.

694
00:35:08,932 --> 00:35:10,394
Uh, headphones should be
on the bench.

695
00:35:10,431 --> 00:35:12,365
Find a seat in the back.
Just get comfortable.

696
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:14,967
You can stand if you want.
Just hold on really tight.

697
00:35:15,003 --> 00:35:16,637
And we'll get going in a minute.

698
00:35:16,671 --> 00:35:18,133
S-sit down.

699
00:35:18,170 --> 00:35:20,539
(engine sputtering)

700
00:35:23,173 --> 00:35:24,639
(engine starts)

701
00:35:24,673 --> 00:35:28,016
BOAT DRIVER:
And we're sailing away.

702
00:35:28,050 --> 00:35:30,820
(duck quacking sound effects
blasting)

703
00:35:30,854 --> 00:35:32,648
Okay, so,
I'll be your guide today

704
00:35:32,684 --> 00:35:36,150
as we cruise along
the great Plummerville lakes.

705
00:35:36,186 --> 00:35:37,349
And, uh...

706
00:35:37,385 --> 00:35:38,659
What's up, guys?

707
00:35:38,695 --> 00:35:40,592
More than you know.

708
00:35:41,766 --> 00:35:43,889
Yeah. You were told to leave.

709
00:35:43,925 --> 00:35:47,929
So what are you still doing
in town, old man?

710
00:35:49,365 --> 00:35:51,836
I'm here with my family,

711
00:35:51,873 --> 00:35:54,036
making memories.

712
00:35:54,072 --> 00:35:55,777
(laughing)

713
00:35:55,813 --> 00:35:57,704
He's making memories, huh?

714
00:35:57,738 --> 00:35:59,378
HUTCH:
There's no need for this.

715
00:35:59,414 --> 00:36:02,617
This is all a big
misunderstanding. I'm here...

716
00:36:02,653 --> 00:36:05,079
(yelling, grunting)

717
00:36:05,115 --> 00:36:06,182
Be cool.

718
00:36:06,217 --> 00:36:07,420
- (groans)
- (clangs)

719
00:36:08,318 --> 00:36:10,083
(grunting, panting)

720
00:36:10,724 --> 00:36:12,260
Come on!

721
00:36:16,063 --> 00:36:18,057
- Hey!
- Use your words.

722
00:36:20,233 --> 00:36:21,963
- (yells)
- (knife clatters)

723
00:36:26,903 --> 00:36:29,309
What am I paying you for?
Fuck. He's right there!

724
00:36:29,344 --> 00:36:32,412
("When the Saints Go
Marchin' In" playing)

725
00:36:39,153 --> 00:36:40,617
BOAT DRIVER:
That's right.

726
00:36:40,653 --> 00:36:42,588
My favorite, personally,
is the butter brownie.

727
00:36:42,623 --> 00:36:45,085
Oh, and, um, speaking of...
(continues indistinctly)

728
00:36:48,655 --> 00:36:50,199
(Hutch grunts fiercely)

729
00:36:52,264 --> 00:36:53,999
Now no one gets the pole.

730
00:36:54,036 --> 00:36:55,633
But I got a fucking knife!

731
00:36:57,804 --> 00:36:59,505
(groans)

732
00:37:00,369 --> 00:37:02,036
(straining)

733
00:37:03,606 --> 00:37:05,874
You're dead, motherfucker.

734
00:37:07,845 --> 00:37:10,911
These waters are home
to our native giant bass.

735
00:37:10,945 --> 00:37:12,780
- (grunts fiercely)
- Cool it, man. Cool it.

736
00:37:12,816 --> 00:37:16,019
Talk to me, okay?
Think of the children.

737
00:37:16,054 --> 00:37:17,688
What?

738
00:37:19,356 --> 00:37:21,396
(distorted groaning)

739
00:37:23,130 --> 00:37:25,601
(distorted):
Fuck.

740
00:37:25,635 --> 00:37:27,731
(straining)

741
00:37:32,974 --> 00:37:34,507
You motherfuck...

742
00:37:42,186 --> 00:37:43,778
That's what I'm
fucking talking about!

743
00:37:43,813 --> 00:37:46,152
You said he was just
a fucking tourist!

744
00:37:46,186 --> 00:37:48,720
That's all Abel fucking told me.

745
00:37:48,755 --> 00:37:51,517
You're gonna pay us a lot more
fucking money now, Dann.

746
00:37:51,552 --> 00:37:53,153
I lost a tooth.

747
00:37:54,161 --> 00:37:55,990
(splashing, thumping)

748
00:37:58,867 --> 00:38:00,998
♪ ♪

749
00:38:01,034 --> 00:38:03,767
(grunting)

750
00:38:10,746 --> 00:38:13,074
(yells)

751
00:38:20,251 --> 00:38:21,552
(muffled grunting)

752
00:38:21,586 --> 00:38:23,787
(distorted duck quacking
sound effects)

753
00:38:33,934 --> 00:38:35,403
(screams)

754
00:38:37,775 --> 00:38:40,338
Ah, fuck that! (screams)

755
00:38:40,373 --> 00:38:42,938
- (whirring)
- (screams) Shit!

756
00:38:43,581 --> 00:38:45,447
(yells)

757
00:38:49,610 --> 00:38:51,853
Tell your boss

758
00:38:51,889 --> 00:38:54,347
I'm... on... fucking...

759
00:38:54,382 --> 00:38:56,450
vacation!

760
00:38:56,487 --> 00:38:59,251
(grunting fiercely)

761
00:39:00,662 --> 00:39:02,695
(flies buzzing)
WOMAN: So, we went to the beach,

762
00:39:02,729 --> 00:39:04,693
now we're gonna get some
ice cream. What flavors? Yeah?

763
00:39:04,728 --> 00:39:06,862
GIRL:
Yeah, I want ice cream.

764
00:39:06,896 --> 00:39:08,963
- I want chocolate ice cream.
- (flies buzzing)

765
00:39:08,998 --> 00:39:10,566
We're gonna get
some chocolate ice cream.

766
00:39:10,601 --> 00:39:12,099
Come on.
Let's go this way. Yeah?

767
00:39:12,133 --> 00:39:14,403
Yeah. Okay. I'm gonna
get strawberry ice cream.

768
00:39:14,438 --> 00:39:16,242
Yeah, and vanilla.

769
00:39:16,277 --> 00:39:18,677
(playing meditative melody)

770
00:39:23,153 --> 00:39:24,612
HUTCH (over speaker):
Hey, Harry.

771
00:39:24,646 --> 00:39:26,653
That wasn't a trumpet.

772
00:39:26,688 --> 00:39:29,159
You were just being serenaded
by a shamisen, my brother.

773
00:39:29,193 --> 00:39:31,719
Ah, you just got back
from Osaka, right?

774
00:39:31,753 --> 00:39:33,791
Yeah, and I master shit quickly.

775
00:39:34,789 --> 00:39:36,590
- What's up?
- Hey.

776
00:39:36,626 --> 00:39:38,496
You remember Plummerville?

777
00:39:38,532 --> 00:39:40,295
One of the happiest weeks
of my life.

778
00:39:40,331 --> 00:39:42,001
Yeah. Mine, too.

779
00:39:42,037 --> 00:39:44,066
Yeah, I remember...

780
00:39:44,101 --> 00:39:46,570
I remember seeing the
other kids and their parents

781
00:39:46,606 --> 00:39:50,302
and thinking
we were just like them.

782
00:39:52,315 --> 00:39:56,385
Anyway, I came back here,
and, um...

783
00:39:57,847 --> 00:39:59,581
Plummerville just isn't
as friendly

784
00:39:59,615 --> 00:40:02,287
as I remember it to be.

785
00:40:02,322 --> 00:40:03,684
It's an old trade route.

786
00:40:03,720 --> 00:40:05,851
Used since the bootlegging days.

787
00:40:05,887 --> 00:40:07,624
Why you think Dad took us there

788
00:40:07,659 --> 00:40:09,728
for our one and only
family vacation?

789
00:40:10,728 --> 00:40:13,363
Are you saying
he was on a mission?

790
00:40:13,398 --> 00:40:15,604
You got it, Hutchy boy.

791
00:40:15,639 --> 00:40:17,336
Oh, yeah.

792
00:40:17,371 --> 00:40:18,867
HARRY:
<i>The cops over there,</i>

793
00:40:18,903 --> 00:40:21,166
<i>they in cahoots
with the big syndicate.</i>

794
00:40:21,202 --> 00:40:23,537
Hey, careful with that.
It's not my money.

795
00:40:23,572 --> 00:40:24,972
I'm sorry, boss.

796
00:40:25,007 --> 00:40:26,811
- I didn't mean to...
- Fucking moron.

797
00:40:26,847 --> 00:40:28,807
HARRY: <i>And they
would not want a guy like you</i>

798
00:40:28,842 --> 00:40:30,449
<i>sniffing around, bro.</i>

799
00:40:30,485 --> 00:40:32,521
(indistinct shouting,
busy chatter)

800
00:40:38,423 --> 00:40:40,360
How's it going?

801
00:40:40,396 --> 00:40:43,092
Holy shit,
this is a big shipment.

802
00:40:45,200 --> 00:40:46,632
What's in the blinking thing?

803
00:40:46,666 --> 00:40:48,365
WYATT: The shit that's
gonna land Lendina

804
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:49,695
on Interpol's top ten.

805
00:40:49,731 --> 00:40:51,771
(both chuckle)

806
00:40:52,778 --> 00:40:54,338
This is great.

807
00:40:54,374 --> 00:40:55,871
You want more guys here

808
00:40:55,905 --> 00:40:57,545
just in case there's
any more trouble?

809
00:40:59,574 --> 00:41:01,242
Hey.

810
00:41:01,278 --> 00:41:04,085
Don't cause any trouble,
and there won't be any trouble.

811
00:41:04,119 --> 00:41:06,213
Remember who's boss here.

812
00:41:07,791 --> 00:41:09,117
Got it.

813
00:41:11,753 --> 00:41:13,429
I got to get my son.

814
00:41:15,132 --> 00:41:17,226
Watch this shit and be cool.

815
00:41:17,262 --> 00:41:19,293
♪ ♪

816
00:41:25,735 --> 00:41:27,501
Want me to take that?

817
00:41:27,537 --> 00:41:29,840
Uh, thanks.

818
00:41:29,876 --> 00:41:31,838
Do you think Dad is
eventually gonna grace us

819
00:41:31,873 --> 00:41:33,673
with his presence or...

820
00:41:33,708 --> 00:41:35,449
Wild animals!

821
00:41:35,485 --> 00:41:37,249
CARNIE:
Whoa. Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

822
00:41:37,284 --> 00:41:38,449
Don't go too near.

823
00:41:38,483 --> 00:41:39,847
That's a wild wolf dog.

824
00:41:39,882 --> 00:41:42,691
Got to stay locked up, that one.

825
00:41:42,726 --> 00:41:45,385
Well, Mom, you saved animals
back when you met Dad, right?

826
00:41:46,461 --> 00:41:48,563
Uh, among other things,
but, um...

827
00:41:48,597 --> 00:41:50,594
(yelps) -You know,
if you gain their trust...

828
00:41:50,630 --> 00:41:51,960
- (barks)
- ...and you show them

829
00:41:51,996 --> 00:41:53,695
that the world is
a safe place for them...

830
00:41:53,729 --> 00:41:55,970
A world that is safe?

831
00:41:56,007 --> 00:41:57,804
What world is that?

832
00:41:59,166 --> 00:42:01,603
Okay. Let's go find Dad
for dinner.

833
00:42:01,637 --> 00:42:03,612
(phone vibrating)

834
00:42:05,478 --> 00:42:07,280
You caught our tourist, I heard.

835
00:42:07,316 --> 00:42:09,085
Did he put up much of a fight?

836
00:42:09,119 --> 00:42:11,978
(power tools buzzing loudly)

837
00:42:12,012 --> 00:42:14,414
What's... I can't hear you.

838
00:42:15,784 --> 00:42:17,925
Hey, turn that off.

839
00:42:17,961 --> 00:42:19,427
Shut it off!

840
00:42:19,461 --> 00:42:21,590
- What are you, new?
- (buzzing stops)

841
00:42:21,624 --> 00:42:23,963
Wh-What was that?

842
00:42:23,998 --> 00:42:27,101
DANN (over phone, slurring):
Uh, he broke my teeth, man.

843
00:42:27,137 --> 00:42:28,633
What about your teeth?

844
00:42:28,668 --> 00:42:30,403
(slurring):
He crushed 'em, okay?

845
00:42:30,440 --> 00:42:33,001
He... he just...
he beat everybody.

846
00:42:33,036 --> 00:42:35,775
What the fuck
are you talking about?

847
00:42:36,840 --> 00:42:38,347
Talking about the guy, okay?

848
00:42:38,382 --> 00:42:40,411
I don't think
he's just some tourist.

849
00:42:40,445 --> 00:42:42,474
(phone ringing)

850
00:42:47,648 --> 00:42:49,083
Yes.

851
00:42:49,119 --> 00:42:50,851
HUTCH (over phone):
I've got a problem.

852
00:42:50,887 --> 00:42:53,329
Of your own making, I sense.

853
00:42:53,363 --> 00:42:55,791
HUTCH:
Plummerville. You heard of it?

854
00:42:55,827 --> 00:42:57,199
THE BARBER:
It's a back road.

855
00:42:57,233 --> 00:43:00,195
Drugs, guns, viruses and worse

856
00:43:00,231 --> 00:43:03,695
come down from Canada
and go on to points unknown.

857
00:43:03,731 --> 00:43:04,999
All right.

858
00:43:05,034 --> 00:43:07,141
Well, where does
the buck stop here?

859
00:43:07,175 --> 00:43:08,874
There are layers.

860
00:43:09,970 --> 00:43:11,775
Possibly an individual,

861
00:43:11,811 --> 00:43:14,815
a unique individual
called Lendina.

862
00:43:16,380 --> 00:43:17,775
Lendina.

863
00:43:17,811 --> 00:43:19,853
♪ ♪

864
00:43:27,566 --> 00:43:29,764
- LENDINA: Guy in the white?
- GUARD: Yes, ma'am.

865
00:43:33,704 --> 00:43:36,536
- No, no. No new dealer.
- This requires a woman's touch.

866
00:43:36,570 --> 00:43:38,731
But I'm winning.
On a roll here.

867
00:43:38,767 --> 00:43:39,835
Congratulations.

868
00:43:39,869 --> 00:43:42,206
Let's see how your luck goes.

869
00:43:42,242 --> 00:43:43,612
(chuckles)

870
00:43:45,050 --> 00:43:46,912
Beautiful. I split.

871
00:43:47,909 --> 00:43:49,211
LENDINA:
Sure.

872
00:43:50,253 --> 00:43:51,650
- Hit me.
- So how's your trip

873
00:43:51,686 --> 00:43:53,487
- been going so far?
- Shut up and deal.

874
00:43:53,523 --> 00:43:56,148
THE BARBER:
<i>Plummerville is critical</i>

875
00:43:56,182 --> 00:43:57,925
<i>to Lendina's larger empire.</i>

876
00:43:57,961 --> 00:43:59,025
Oh, shit.

877
00:43:59,061 --> 00:44:00,724
Aw.

878
00:44:00,758 --> 00:44:02,755
- (taps on table)
- It happens.

879
00:44:02,791 --> 00:44:04,090
(chips clacking)

880
00:44:04,124 --> 00:44:05,766
THE BARBER:
<i>A lone wolf.</i>

881
00:44:05,802 --> 00:44:11,697
Operates unburdened
by any constraints... at all.

882
00:44:11,733 --> 00:44:14,876
You piss off the Russians, they
come to your house with guns.

883
00:44:14,912 --> 00:44:18,278
Lendina and her squad will slay
your family on the front lawn

884
00:44:18,313 --> 00:44:20,240
and force you to watch

885
00:44:20,277 --> 00:44:24,081
if you disrupt
their situations any further.

886
00:44:28,057 --> 00:44:29,088
Yes.

887
00:44:29,124 --> 00:44:30,454
(laughter)

888
00:44:30,490 --> 00:44:32,856
Pay me. (laughs)

889
00:44:32,891 --> 00:44:34,853
- (screaming)
- (bystanders gasping)

890
00:44:34,889 --> 00:44:36,856
(laughing)

891
00:44:36,891 --> 00:44:39,391
You're a winner.

892
00:44:39,427 --> 00:44:41,427
DEALER: Ma'am, I swear,
I knew nothing...

893
00:44:41,461 --> 00:44:43,738
- (bystanders screaming)
- MAN: Oh, my God!

894
00:44:45,099 --> 00:44:46,307
MAN:
What's happening?

895
00:44:46,342 --> 00:44:47,907
(screaming, frantic chatter)

896
00:44:50,280 --> 00:44:51,876
Nobody cheats in my casino!

897
00:44:51,912 --> 00:44:54,177
- (feedback squealing)
- (men groaning)

898
00:44:56,613 --> 00:44:58,280
(neck snaps)

899
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:03,418
You'll want to de-escalate
the situation.

900
00:45:03,454 --> 00:45:08,257
I mean, do you got any intel,
an... an address or anything?

901
00:45:09,258 --> 00:45:12,492
I'll give you a lead,
but hear me on this.

902
00:45:14,030 --> 00:45:15,633
You're on your own, Hutch.

903
00:45:15,670 --> 00:45:17,329
- Aw, Killer.
- (dog whimpering)

904
00:45:17,365 --> 00:45:20,342
I'm so sorry
that you had to see that.

905
00:45:20,378 --> 00:45:22,233
My little baby should never see

906
00:45:22,269 --> 00:45:24,604
those terrible, terrible people.

907
00:45:24,641 --> 00:45:26,171
No.

908
00:45:26,206 --> 00:45:28,117
What about them back there?

909
00:45:28,153 --> 00:45:29,416
Leave no witnesses.

910
00:45:29,452 --> 00:45:31,445
- Burn it down.
- You got it.

911
00:45:33,191 --> 00:45:34,985
(bystanders screaming)

912
00:45:35,019 --> 00:45:37,220
- (rapid gunfire)
- (screaming continues)

913
00:45:40,825 --> 00:45:43,362
That was fast. Did it hurt?

914
00:45:43,398 --> 00:45:45,300
No, I'm fine.

915
00:45:45,335 --> 00:45:46,697
Maybe this is too soon.

916
00:45:46,731 --> 00:45:48,963
Dad, really, I'm fine.

917
00:45:48,998 --> 00:45:50,999
My arm's healing good.

918
00:45:51,034 --> 00:45:53,710
- (ringtone playing)
- Hold on.

919
00:45:56,744 --> 00:45:58,476
Max, I have to take
this damn call.

920
00:45:58,512 --> 00:45:59,811
Won't be long.

921
00:45:59,847 --> 00:46:00,976
(gunfire and screaming
in distance)

922
00:46:01,010 --> 00:46:02,175
WYATT (over phone):
What?

923
00:46:02,211 --> 00:46:03,717
LENDINA (chuckles):
Well...

924
00:46:03,753 --> 00:46:06,153
that's no way to treat
your business partner.

925
00:46:06,188 --> 00:46:07,885
Ex-partner.

926
00:46:07,921 --> 00:46:09,322
(over phone):
This is my last shipment.

927
00:46:09,358 --> 00:46:11,282
(sighs) Goodness.

928
00:46:11,318 --> 00:46:14,063
My father's debt is all paid up.

929
00:46:14,097 --> 00:46:16,990
I can count.

930
00:46:17,025 --> 00:46:20,295
This, you know...

931
00:46:20,331 --> 00:46:22,630
(choking up):
pays off the last of our debt.

932
00:46:22,666 --> 00:46:24,333
Aw.

933
00:46:24,369 --> 00:46:27,539
By my calculations, the debt
will never be paid off.

934
00:46:27,574 --> 00:46:28,905
(scoffing):
No.

935
00:46:28,941 --> 00:46:30,342
That's bullshit,
and you know it.

936
00:46:30,378 --> 00:46:32,746
(laughing)

937
00:46:32,782 --> 00:46:34,514
Ain't nothing funny
about what I said.

938
00:46:34,550 --> 00:46:36,146
(Lendina laughing over phone)

939
00:46:36,181 --> 00:46:39,583
Your father died
because he was distracted.

940
00:46:39,619 --> 00:46:41,387
Are you distracted?

941
00:46:41,423 --> 00:46:42,849
I'm not my dad.

942
00:46:42,885 --> 00:46:44,425
It's over.

943
00:46:44,461 --> 00:46:46,260
(Lendina scoffs over phone)

944
00:46:46,295 --> 00:46:48,320
Well, then...

945
00:46:48,354 --> 00:46:50,494
- we'll see.
- (phone beeps)

946
00:46:50,528 --> 00:46:52,362
Well...

947
00:46:54,367 --> 00:46:55,804
Hello?

948
00:46:58,603 --> 00:47:00,633
♪ ♪

949
00:47:02,711 --> 00:47:04,740
WYATT:
Hey, Max, where you going?

950
00:47:04,775 --> 00:47:06,639
(door closes)

951
00:47:12,255 --> 00:47:14,715
(phone vibrating)

952
00:47:14,751 --> 00:47:16,418
Sheriff.

953
00:47:16,454 --> 00:47:18,394
SHERIFF ABEL (over phone):
You can just call me Abel.

954
00:47:18,429 --> 00:47:21,025
Sheriff, I need to make sure

955
00:47:21,061 --> 00:47:23,492
Wyatt hasn't forgotten
who he works for.

956
00:47:24,657 --> 00:47:27,960
Take something
that really matters to him.

957
00:47:27,994 --> 00:47:29,498
Got it.

958
00:47:37,010 --> 00:47:39,941
- Mom, it's your turn.
- Oh. (clears throat)

959
00:47:39,978 --> 00:47:41,813
- BRADY: Hey, Mom?
- Yes?

960
00:47:41,849 --> 00:47:44,244
- Is Dad in trouble again?
- Mm.

961
00:47:44,278 --> 00:47:46,119
Why? Do you know something?

962
00:47:47,115 --> 00:47:48,646
No, that's why... No.

963
00:47:48,682 --> 00:47:50,958
- Mm, I'm sure he'll be...
- (knocking at door)

964
00:47:53,264 --> 00:47:54,490
No, honey. Let me.

965
00:48:05,539 --> 00:48:07,476
Hamburgers!

966
00:48:07,512 --> 00:48:10,007
And s'mores for dinner tonight.

967
00:48:10,043 --> 00:48:12,541
- BRADY: Ah, so nutritious.
- SAMMY: Yay.

968
00:48:13,648 --> 00:48:15,811
Your dad's running late.

969
00:48:15,847 --> 00:48:17,653
But come with me.

970
00:48:17,688 --> 00:48:19,452
I promise you
it's the way to go.

971
00:48:19,487 --> 00:48:20,787
(Sammy chuckles)

972
00:48:20,822 --> 00:48:22,318
BRADY: Sammy, come on.
Help me pack up.

973
00:48:22,354 --> 00:48:24,487
- You-you talked to Hutch?
- Talk later. Got to move.

974
00:48:25,461 --> 00:48:26,488
BECCA:
Okay.

975
00:48:27,824 --> 00:48:30,429
(sighs)

976
00:48:30,465 --> 00:48:32,597
Walk in...

977
00:48:32,632 --> 00:48:35,293
real smooth.

978
00:48:35,329 --> 00:48:37,336
Keep everything room temp.

979
00:48:37,371 --> 00:48:38,867
Yeah.

980
00:48:38,903 --> 00:48:40,836
No escalating.

981
00:48:40,871 --> 00:48:43,211
De-escalate.

982
00:48:43,248 --> 00:48:45,445
Lead by example.

983
00:48:45,481 --> 00:48:46,778
(inhales sharply)

984
00:48:46,813 --> 00:48:49,481
"Hey, fellas. What a mix-up."

985
00:48:49,516 --> 00:48:51,546
♪ ♪

986
00:48:53,490 --> 00:48:55,054
It's a big shipment, but...

987
00:48:55,088 --> 00:48:57,153
I guarantee you
we can do more next time.

988
00:48:57,188 --> 00:48:59,188
Except those paintings
are a bitch.

989
00:48:59,224 --> 00:49:01,853
But you got to see
what's in here.

990
00:49:05,231 --> 00:49:09,001
Here is the special thing
the boss lady asked for.

991
00:49:09,037 --> 00:49:10,735
- (muffled grunting)
- Wyatt's spoiled son.

992
00:49:10,771 --> 00:49:12,298
(muffled):
Wait! Wait!

993
00:49:12,333 --> 00:49:14,041
No! Wait! (continues shouting)

994
00:49:14,077 --> 00:49:16,505
Now, I want you to tell
the boss that I said it was

995
00:49:16,541 --> 00:49:18,842
- a pleasure to be of service.
- (banging on van door)

996
00:49:18,878 --> 00:49:21,548
Okay? You understand?

997
00:49:21,583 --> 00:49:23,048
MAX (muffled):
Hey!

998
00:49:23,083 --> 00:49:25,478
Or do I need to get
a fucking translator?

999
00:49:25,514 --> 00:49:27,722
(muffled grunting
and shouting continue)

1000
00:49:27,757 --> 00:49:29,686
I need to get
a fucking translator.

1001
00:49:29,722 --> 00:49:31,887
(liquid pouring)

1002
00:49:31,921 --> 00:49:33,222
Hey, fellas.

1003
00:49:33,257 --> 00:49:35,597
What the fuck?
How did you get in here?

1004
00:49:35,632 --> 00:49:37,860
- The door.
- (guns cocking)

1005
00:49:37,896 --> 00:49:39,499
Is that gasoline?

1006
00:49:39,534 --> 00:49:41,233
You're quick.

1007
00:49:45,534 --> 00:49:47,874
Now, listen,
I could torch this money,

1008
00:49:47,909 --> 00:49:49,610
it'd go up in a flash,
and whatever's

1009
00:49:49,646 --> 00:49:51,407
in those barrels would go boom,

1010
00:49:51,443 --> 00:49:53,443
and most of you
wouldn't make it out of here,

1011
00:49:53,478 --> 00:49:56,952
and those who do
will have to answer to Lendina.

1012
00:49:58,083 --> 00:50:00,583
I'm guessing this is all hers.

1013
00:50:01,956 --> 00:50:04,487
So then what the fuck
do you want?

1014
00:50:06,429 --> 00:50:08,463
Okay, well...

1015
00:50:08,498 --> 00:50:10,088
I want a break.

1016
00:50:10,124 --> 00:50:11,291
A break?

1017
00:50:11,327 --> 00:50:14,635
I just want a fucking break.

1018
00:50:14,670 --> 00:50:16,903
So if I walk out of here,

1019
00:50:16,938 --> 00:50:19,574
you leave me
and my family alone,

1020
00:50:19,608 --> 00:50:21,365
'cause that's all I want.

1021
00:50:21,402 --> 00:50:23,278
To de-escalate this.

1022
00:50:23,313 --> 00:50:25,074
(scoffs)

1023
00:50:25,110 --> 00:50:27,615
Are you fucking kidding me?

1024
00:50:27,650 --> 00:50:29,081
From the moment you've shown up,

1025
00:50:29,115 --> 00:50:31,315
you've put my men
in the fucking ER.

1026
00:50:31,351 --> 00:50:33,780
There's no way
you are just some family man.

1027
00:50:35,316 --> 00:50:38,057
De-escalate? Fuck you.

1028
00:50:38,094 --> 00:50:40,755
Plummerville was A-OK
before you showed up.

1029
00:50:41,762 --> 00:50:43,626
Wherever I go...

1030
00:50:44,867 --> 00:50:48,103
I could so easily
kill you right now.

1031
00:50:49,273 --> 00:50:51,139
But...

1032
00:50:55,380 --> 00:50:56,804
You're lucky.

1033
00:50:57,780 --> 00:51:00,181
You catch me on a good day.

1034
00:51:03,452 --> 00:51:05,014
Go.

1035
00:51:05,050 --> 00:51:06,880
Get the fuck out of here.

1036
00:51:09,220 --> 00:51:11,488
Go before I change my mind.

1037
00:51:12,891 --> 00:51:14,860
(guns clicking)

1038
00:51:14,894 --> 00:51:17,188
(banging on van door)

1039
00:51:17,224 --> 00:51:19,362
(grunts)

1040
00:51:19,396 --> 00:51:21,126
SHERIFF ABEL:
Fucking pick him up.

1041
00:51:21,162 --> 00:51:22,429
Jesus.

1042
00:51:22,463 --> 00:51:25,130
MAX (muffled):
No! Help me!

1043
00:51:25,166 --> 00:51:26,474
Help me!

1044
00:51:26,508 --> 00:51:28,874
No! (shouts)

1045
00:51:28,909 --> 00:51:32,411
(muffled shouting continues)

1046
00:51:41,414 --> 00:51:43,586
(engine starts)

1047
00:51:50,666 --> 00:51:53,061
(tires screech)

1048
00:51:53,097 --> 00:51:54,927
(engine revving)

1049
00:52:01,938 --> 00:52:03,673
(sighs)

1050
00:52:06,115 --> 00:52:08,179
SHERIFF ABEL:
You're on my last fucking nerve.

1051
00:52:08,215 --> 00:52:09,983
I told you
to get the fuck out...

1052
00:52:10,019 --> 00:52:11,679
- (clattering)
- (men yelling, groaning)

1053
00:52:11,713 --> 00:52:13,749
- (rapid gunfire)
- Who the fuck is this guy?!

1054
00:52:18,121 --> 00:52:20,356
(men yelling)

1055
00:52:20,392 --> 00:52:22,090
- SHERIFF ABEL: Wait! Wait!
- (gunshots)

1056
00:52:22,126 --> 00:52:24,324
(men screaming)

1057
00:52:24,360 --> 00:52:26,932
(gunfire continues)

1058
00:52:26,967 --> 00:52:29,231
(grunting and groaning)

1059
00:52:29,266 --> 00:52:31,700
(Max gasping, breathing heavily)

1060
00:52:33,541 --> 00:52:35,309
(choking)

1061
00:52:47,720 --> 00:52:49,615
(choking)

1062
00:52:49,652 --> 00:52:52,161
(Max whimpering,
breathing heavily)

1063
00:53:02,295 --> 00:53:04,197
(gasping)

1064
00:53:04,233 --> 00:53:05,630
(man yells)

1065
00:53:05,666 --> 00:53:08,507
(grunting and groaning continue)

1066
00:53:10,976 --> 00:53:13,072
(whirring)

1067
00:53:14,407 --> 00:53:16,646
(straining)

1068
00:53:27,630 --> 00:53:29,528
(blade whining)

1069
00:53:30,963 --> 00:53:32,590
(whining stops)

1070
00:53:32,626 --> 00:53:35,434
(Max gasping, whimpering)

1071
00:53:38,941 --> 00:53:41,441
HUTCH:
(grunts) Okay, let's go.

1072
00:53:44,505 --> 00:53:46,874
(pained grunting)

1073
00:53:50,449 --> 00:53:52,815
- Stop, motherfucker!
- (gun fires)

1074
00:53:53,822 --> 00:53:54,949
(gun clicking)

1075
00:53:56,123 --> 00:53:58,150
- (clicking)
- (grunts, pants)

1076
00:53:59,726 --> 00:54:01,262
(groans)

1077
00:54:01,296 --> 00:54:04,155
("If I Ruled the World"
by Tony Bennett playing)

1078
00:54:12,740 --> 00:54:14,838
(panting)

1079
00:54:14,873 --> 00:54:19,005
- ♪ If I ruled the world ♪
- SHERIFF ABEL: Fuck! Fuck!

1080
00:54:20,811 --> 00:54:26,255
♪ Every day would be
the first day of spring ♪

1081
00:54:27,981 --> 00:54:31,652
♪ Every heart would have
a new song ♪

1082
00:54:31,688 --> 00:54:33,559
- ♪ To sing ♪
- Fuck! Fuck!

1083
00:54:36,164 --> 00:54:39,726
♪ And we'd sing of the joy ♪

1084
00:54:39,762 --> 00:54:43,833
♪ Every morning would bring ♪

1085
00:54:45,537 --> 00:54:48,277
- ♪ If I... ♪
- (song fades)

1086
00:54:51,916 --> 00:54:53,141
LENDINA:
How much did we lose?

1087
00:54:53,177 --> 00:54:54,510
Everything.

1088
00:54:54,546 --> 00:54:56,583
- The cash, the chemicals.
- The bio-case.

1089
00:54:56,619 --> 00:54:58,181
No.

1090
00:54:58,217 --> 00:54:59,481
GUARD:
All of it.

1091
00:54:59,516 --> 00:55:00,889
GUARD 2:
Wiped out all our men

1092
00:55:00,923 --> 00:55:02,885
and got away with Wyatt's son.

1093
00:55:07,963 --> 00:55:09,722
Who is this zealot?

1094
00:55:09,757 --> 00:55:11,523
Nothing about him is turning up.

1095
00:55:11,559 --> 00:55:13,599
There is one oddity.

1096
00:55:14,728 --> 00:55:17,095
He had a family with him.

1097
00:55:17,130 --> 00:55:21,204
LENDINA: My valuable shipment
was blown up

1098
00:55:21,240 --> 00:55:24,110
by a man who's a tourist

1099
00:55:24,144 --> 00:55:27,139
on a fucking family vacation?

1100
00:55:29,382 --> 00:55:32,017
Does nobody play
by the rules anymore?

1101
00:55:32,052 --> 00:55:35,057
Jesus fucking Christ.

1102
00:55:35,092 --> 00:55:36,782
I don't know
who the fuck you are,

1103
00:55:36,816 --> 00:55:38,454
but you crossed a line, asshole.

1104
00:55:38,488 --> 00:55:40,889
- (phone vibrating)
- Sheriff.

1105
00:55:43,496 --> 00:55:45,392
What do you know
about this threat?

1106
00:55:45,429 --> 00:55:47,693
I don't know, okay?

1107
00:55:47,728 --> 00:55:49,269
But I sent you the pictures.

1108
00:55:49,304 --> 00:55:51,405
And they haven't checked out
of the hotel.

1109
00:55:51,441 --> 00:55:53,074
You might want to bring
some others, all right?

1110
00:55:53,110 --> 00:55:55,943
H-How many of your...
I guess soldiers

1111
00:55:55,978 --> 00:55:57,376
can you bring with you?

1112
00:55:57,411 --> 00:55:59,648
- Because he's...
- Oh, shut the fuck up.

1113
00:55:59,684 --> 00:56:01,606
I'm on my way.

1114
00:56:01,642 --> 00:56:03,682
This guy's an idiot.

1115
00:56:05,655 --> 00:56:07,052
Hey, son.

1116
00:56:07,088 --> 00:56:08,284
Look who finally shows up.

1117
00:56:08,320 --> 00:56:10,322
Hey, Dad. Everybody good?

1118
00:56:10,358 --> 00:56:13,095
DAVID:
Oh, everybody's doing great.

1119
00:56:13,130 --> 00:56:16,994
Your son swings an axe
like a pro.

1120
00:56:17,030 --> 00:56:18,329
SAMMY:
Dad.

1121
00:56:18,365 --> 00:56:20,126
- Sammy.
- SAMMY: Where were you?

1122
00:56:21,103 --> 00:56:22,728
Oh, hey, Brady, that's Max.

1123
00:56:22,764 --> 00:56:25,197
I brought him here, so be cool.

1124
00:56:30,613 --> 00:56:32,108
We good?

1125
00:56:32,142 --> 00:56:33,673
Yeah.

1126
00:56:33,708 --> 00:56:35,414
BRADY:
Let's go inside.

1127
00:56:35,449 --> 00:56:37,816
How'd you get that shiner,
country boy?

1128
00:56:37,851 --> 00:56:38,920
Kidding.

1129
00:56:38,956 --> 00:56:40,284
You staying for the night?

1130
00:56:40,320 --> 00:56:43,157
I-I would love to stay, but, um,

1131
00:56:43,193 --> 00:56:45,487
I still got some
heavy lifting to do.

1132
00:56:45,523 --> 00:56:46,862
(chuckling):
Oh, you're...

1133
00:56:46,896 --> 00:56:48,363
you're right about that.

1134
00:56:53,363 --> 00:56:55,934
Let's go, Sammy.

1135
00:56:55,969 --> 00:56:57,938
Come on.

1136
00:56:57,974 --> 00:57:00,409
You can light the fire.

1137
00:57:02,470 --> 00:57:04,478
(sighs)

1138
00:57:09,478 --> 00:57:10,851
(Becca scoffs)

1139
00:57:10,887 --> 00:57:12,849
Arm's length, Hutch.

1140
00:57:12,885 --> 00:57:15,889
You were supposed to keep
danger at arm's length.

1141
00:57:15,925 --> 00:57:17,822
I didn't mean to...

1142
00:57:18,753 --> 00:57:21,528
Hutch, you promised me.

1143
00:57:22,525 --> 00:57:24,463
You promised.

1144
00:57:24,498 --> 00:57:27,358
(sniffles)
You broke your promise.

1145
00:57:29,697 --> 00:57:32,699
I don't have...

1146
00:57:32,733 --> 00:57:35,141
have control over this.

1147
00:57:35,175 --> 00:57:37,472
I'm just realizing that.

1148
00:57:37,507 --> 00:57:40,010
You should get away...

1149
00:57:40,045 --> 00:57:42,574
(sighs)

1150
00:57:42,610 --> 00:57:44,342
...from me.

1151
00:57:46,085 --> 00:57:47,887
(sighs)

1152
00:57:47,921 --> 00:57:49,590
Becca.

1153
00:57:50,961 --> 00:57:53,758
Becca, I'm not asking.

1154
00:57:57,066 --> 00:57:59,291
You don't tell me what to do.

1155
00:58:00,532 --> 00:58:03,499
You are a lot of things...

1156
00:58:03,534 --> 00:58:06,068
but most of all, you're a dad.

1157
00:58:07,074 --> 00:58:08,807
And you're my guy.

1158
00:58:10,079 --> 00:58:11,644
So go fix that shit.

1159
00:58:18,713 --> 00:58:20,086
Come on, son.

1160
00:58:20,121 --> 00:58:22,682
Answer your damn phone.

1161
00:58:22,719 --> 00:58:24,954
Come on, come on, come on.

1162
00:58:28,063 --> 00:58:29,931
(cork pops from bottle)

1163
00:58:29,965 --> 00:58:31,994
(drink pouring)

1164
00:58:38,940 --> 00:58:40,474
You.

1165
00:58:40,510 --> 00:58:42,572
What the hell are you
still doing in my town?

1166
00:58:42,606 --> 00:58:44,405
Well, I could use your help.

1167
00:58:44,441 --> 00:58:45,780
(grunting)

1168
00:58:45,816 --> 00:58:47,610
Oh, no, no.

1169
00:58:47,644 --> 00:58:49,441
Be cool. I've got your son.

1170
00:58:50,452 --> 00:58:52,447
- He's okay.
- You mess with my son,

1171
00:58:52,483 --> 00:58:53,648
you're a dead man.

1172
00:58:53,682 --> 00:58:55,421
No, you don't understand.

1173
00:58:55,456 --> 00:58:57,423
He's totally safe
with some people...

1174
00:58:57,458 --> 00:58:59,719
What the fuck
do you mean by safe?

1175
00:58:59,753 --> 00:59:01,588
(both grunting)

1176
00:59:01,624 --> 00:59:03,757
From Lendina.

1177
00:59:03,791 --> 00:59:05,699
(Wyatt breathing heavily)

1178
00:59:06,829 --> 00:59:10,329
We want the same things.
(grunts)

1179
00:59:18,474 --> 00:59:20,273
(sighs)

1180
00:59:21,644 --> 00:59:23,309
You burned all of it?

1181
00:59:24,315 --> 00:59:25,514
Yep.

1182
00:59:25,550 --> 00:59:26,851
You burned the money?

1183
00:59:28,217 --> 00:59:30,287
And whatever was in
those chemical barrels.

1184
00:59:30,322 --> 00:59:32,191
Th-they exploded.

1185
00:59:32,226 --> 00:59:33,621
You burned all of it?

1186
00:59:33,657 --> 00:59:35,960
I-I saved your son.

1187
00:59:37,900 --> 00:59:39,193
Thanks.

1188
00:59:40,994 --> 00:59:44,298
She's pure fucking evil, man.

1189
00:59:45,304 --> 00:59:47,338
She killed my dad.

1190
00:59:47,374 --> 00:59:49,402
Used Abel to take my son.

1191
00:59:50,905 --> 00:59:52,976
Backstabbing son of a bitch.

1192
01:00:02,316 --> 01:00:06,985
This empire that I inherited
from my dad

1193
01:00:07,019 --> 01:00:09,157
came with a lot of debts.

1194
01:00:10,229 --> 01:00:12,061
Wild Bill.

1195
01:00:12,097 --> 01:00:15,427
He was a lot of fun,
but the man liked the bad odds.

1196
01:00:18,869 --> 01:00:22,369
And I'm still paying
for his mistakes.

1197
01:00:22,403 --> 01:00:26,371
Lendina has run this town
for two fucking generations.

1198
01:00:26,405 --> 01:00:29,045
I will not let my son
be forced into this.

1199
01:00:30,945 --> 01:00:32,412
I know what you mean.

1200
01:00:38,293 --> 01:00:39,889
So wh-what would she do

1201
01:00:39,923 --> 01:00:42,260
if she found out
you burned her stash?

1202
01:00:42,295 --> 01:00:44,362
You burned it.

1203
01:00:44,398 --> 01:00:46,865
Okay. What would she do?

1204
01:00:48,898 --> 01:00:51,563
("Das Boot" by Beginner playing)

1205
01:00:53,210 --> 01:00:55,202
Okay, how-how do I put this?

1206
01:00:55,237 --> 01:00:57,101
♪ Dope dope beat beat,
dope dope... ♪

1207
01:00:57,137 --> 01:00:58,905
WYATT:
<i>She's eradicated</i>

1208
01:00:58,941 --> 01:01:01,309
<i>entire bloodlines for less.</i>

1209
01:01:02,309 --> 01:01:05,380
<i>She's absolutely batshit crazy.</i>

1210
01:01:05,416 --> 01:01:06,552
Vicious.

1211
01:01:06,586 --> 01:01:08,556
♪ Dope dope rhymes rhymes ♪

1212
01:01:08,592 --> 01:01:11,686
♪ Dope dope, dope dope,
dope dope... ♪

1213
01:01:11,722 --> 01:01:14,052
Where is she right now?

1214
01:01:14,088 --> 01:01:16,255
She's definitely
on her way here.

1215
01:01:16,291 --> 01:01:19,063
(song continues
with lyrics in German)

1216
01:01:20,267 --> 01:01:22,231
Ma'am, it's time.

1217
01:01:25,298 --> 01:01:27,304
- (song stops)
- (elevator rattling)

1218
01:01:27,340 --> 01:01:28,907
(dog whines)

1219
01:01:32,081 --> 01:01:34,474
♪ ♪

1220
01:01:37,485 --> 01:01:39,043
LENDINA:
Hit it, motherfuckers.

1221
01:01:39,079 --> 01:01:40,318
KARTOUSH:
Let's move.

1222
01:01:40,353 --> 01:01:42,416
(engines revving)

1223
01:01:49,257 --> 01:01:52,463
WYATT: My dad planned
to fight Lendina.

1224
01:01:52,499 --> 01:01:55,162
She got to him first.

1225
01:01:55,197 --> 01:01:58,266
I'm not sure
if any of it still works.

1226
01:02:02,110 --> 01:02:03,976
I wouldn't.

1227
01:02:07,008 --> 01:02:08,440
WYATT:
<i>Now we lead her to</i>

1228
01:02:08,474 --> 01:02:10,112
<i>the most dangerous place
in Plummerville.</i>

1229
01:02:10,148 --> 01:02:11,985
- Closed for repairs.
- Hey, we just got here.

1230
01:02:12,021 --> 01:02:14,115
So sorry, folks, but it's got
to be made safe. Here you go.

1231
01:02:14,152 --> 01:02:15,690
- You got free churros.
- Your website didn't say

1232
01:02:15,726 --> 01:02:16,949
- anything about...
- You're gonna get a free refund.

1233
01:02:16,985 --> 01:02:18,255
Let's go! Let's go now!

1234
01:02:18,291 --> 01:02:20,322
♪ ♪

1235
01:02:26,231 --> 01:02:28,626
Must be hard to say goodbye
to this place, huh?

1236
01:02:28,662 --> 01:02:30,836
(scoffs) -You know,
when my dad brought us here,

1237
01:02:30,871 --> 01:02:32,869
- these rides...
- You kidding me? It's a curse.

1238
01:02:32,905 --> 01:02:34,608
Water park leaks
like a motherfucker.

1239
01:02:34,642 --> 01:02:36,269
The fun house is nothing
but headaches.

1240
01:02:36,304 --> 01:02:38,436
No kid wants exactly
what their dad built.

1241
01:02:38,472 --> 01:02:41,007
Really?
That's actually good to hear.

1242
01:02:41,041 --> 01:02:42,751
Who the fuck is that?

1243
01:02:44,186 --> 01:02:45,985
HUTCH:
Harry?

1244
01:02:46,021 --> 01:02:48,354
You know, this place is much
smaller than I remember, man.

1245
01:02:48,389 --> 01:02:50,559
(laughing):
Oh, man.

1246
01:02:50,594 --> 01:02:53,353
- This is my brother Harry.
- Wyatt Martin.

1247
01:02:53,387 --> 01:02:55,191
- Good to meet you.
- What are you doing here?

1248
01:02:55,226 --> 01:02:57,889
I sensed you was having
an existential crisis.

1249
01:02:57,925 --> 01:02:59,999
♪ ♪

1250
01:03:09,045 --> 01:03:10,074
(grunting)

1251
01:03:22,458 --> 01:03:23,851
Okay, I want to talk to you.

1252
01:03:23,885 --> 01:03:25,358
Hey. (whistles)

1253
01:03:25,392 --> 01:03:27,152
Yeah. Good boy.

1254
01:03:27,186 --> 01:03:28,691
Yeah, go on. Go on. Go.

1255
01:03:28,726 --> 01:03:30,722
(wolf dog howling)

1256
01:03:35,699 --> 01:03:37,728
(grunting)

1257
01:03:45,642 --> 01:03:47,706
♪ ♪

1258
01:04:11,737 --> 01:04:14,965
(lighter clinks, ignites)

1259
01:04:15,001 --> 01:04:17,436
You know, Pops, remember that
you left us alone in that lodge

1260
01:04:17,472 --> 01:04:19,275
for two nights straight
by ourselves.

1261
01:04:19,309 --> 01:04:22,141
And all we had to eat
was hot dogs and s'mores.

1262
01:04:22,177 --> 01:04:24,077
That's partly why I'm a vegan.

1263
01:04:24,112 --> 01:04:27,912
Well, you guys were safe.

1264
01:04:27,947 --> 01:04:29,824
Mostly.

1265
01:04:29,858 --> 01:04:32,251
Did you ever worry
about us, though? I mean...

1266
01:04:32,286 --> 01:04:34,662
like about who we'd become.

1267
01:04:34,697 --> 01:04:36,764
You mean like
how you worry about Brady?

1268
01:04:36,798 --> 01:04:39,630
- Yeah. I want him to be...
- (David chuckles)

1269
01:04:39,666 --> 01:04:41,465
A better man than you.

1270
01:04:41,499 --> 01:04:42,963
Yeah.

1271
01:04:42,998 --> 01:04:45,162
And he will be.

1272
01:04:45,197 --> 01:04:47,639
Believe it or not,

1273
01:04:47,675 --> 01:04:53,103
you guys are improvements on me.

1274
01:04:53,139 --> 01:04:54,909
(chuckling)

1275
01:04:54,945 --> 01:04:56,344
HUTCH:
Hey, listen.

1276
01:04:56,378 --> 01:04:57,981
- You know where you're headed?
- I got it.

1277
01:04:58,016 --> 01:04:59,983
Okay.
You need any help up there?

1278
01:05:00,019 --> 01:05:03,354
Yeah, I got something,
uh, else in mind.

1279
01:05:03,391 --> 01:05:05,454
♪ ♪

1280
01:05:13,170 --> 01:05:15,662
Time's up!

1281
01:05:25,746 --> 01:05:27,476
They're in the water park.

1282
01:05:28,382 --> 01:05:30,182
Fun.

1283
01:05:31,853 --> 01:05:33,686
- What's that?
- Some sort of cabin.

1284
01:05:33,720 --> 01:05:35,516
We think his family's there.

1285
01:05:37,019 --> 01:05:38,887
Take a team and go there.

1286
01:05:38,923 --> 01:05:40,691
- And, Kartoush...
- Yes?

1287
01:05:40,726 --> 01:05:42,791
Scorched earth.

1288
01:05:42,827 --> 01:05:44,798
No prisoners.

1289
01:05:44,833 --> 01:05:47,130
...then open it
and put chocolate inside?

1290
01:05:47,166 --> 01:05:49,597
(conversation continues
indistinctly)

